SIMPLE: cobbler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cobbler
<hw>Cob"bler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A mender
of shoes.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A clumsy workman.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A beverage. See <cref>Sherry cobbler</cref>, under
<er>Sherry</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cobbler fish</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a marine
fish (<spn>Blepharis crinitus</spn>) of the Atlantic. The name alludes
to its threadlike fin rays.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cobblestone</ent>⟦br⟧
